      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel like your presence is a burden, especially when you love your daughter so deeply and want her a better life. The math you did highlights the reality of a \"debt trap,\" but it doesn't mean there is no path out; sometimes the solution requires help trying options you can't see when stressed. Consider exploring a credit counseling agency specifically for severe financial distress or looking into family leave services where the kids might care for themselves for a while, giving you time to restructure your income. Please remember that asking for guidance from a financial therapist today could change your entire perspective on what is actually happening.",
